text: The 2014 South Australian state election was held on 15 March 2014 to elect the 53rd Parliament of South Australia, including all 47 seats in the House of Assembly and 11 of the 22 seats in the Legislative Council. It was conducted by the Electoral Commission of South Australia (ECSA). The incumbent Labor government, led by Premier Jay Weatherill, won a fourth term in government. They were opposed by the Liberal Party, led by Steven Marshall. Labor formed a minority government with the support of independent Geoff Brock. ==References== Category:2014 elections in Australia Category:Elections in South Australia Category:2010s in South Australia Category:March 2014 events
